In [[game theory]], a '''Hicks-optimal outcome''', named after [[John Hicks]], is an outcome in which the total payoff for all of the players of a game is the most it could possibly be.  A Hicks-optimal outcome is always [[Pareto efficiency|Pareto efficient]].

