An '''open formula''' is a [[formula (logic)|formula]] that contains at least one [[free variable]].{{citation needed|date=September 2016}} Some educational resources use the term "'''open sentence'''",<ref>http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/53280.html</ref>{{unreliable source|date=October 2016}} but this use conflicts with the definition of "[[sentence (logic)|sentence]]" as a formula that does not contain any free variables.
