{{Infobox scientist | name = Tobias Nipkow | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = 1958 <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | birth_place = | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | residence = [[Munich]] | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = | workplaces = [[MIT]], [[Cambridge University]], [[TU Munich]] | patrons = | alma_mater = | thesis_title = Behavioural Implementation Concepts for Nondeterministic Data Types | thesis_url = http://www.worldcat.org/title/behavioural-implementation-concepts-for-nondeterministic-data-types/oclc/18002367 | thesis_year = 1987 | doctoral_advisor = [[Cliff B. Jones]] | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = [[Isabelle proof assistant]] | influences = | influenced = | awards = | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = {{URL|http://www21.in.tum.de/~nipkow}} | footnotes = }} '''Tobias Nipkow''' (born 1958) is a German computer scientist. He received his [[Diplom]] (MSc) in [[computer science]] from the [[Technische Hochschule Darmstadt]] in 1982, and his Ph.D. from the [[University of Manchester]] in 1987. He worked at [[MIT]] from 1987, changed to [[Cambridge University]] in 1989, and to [[Technical University Munich]] in 1992, where he was appointed professor for programming theory. He is chair of the Logic and Verification group since 2011.
He is known for his work in interactive and automatic theorem proving, in particular for the [[Isabelle proof assistant]]; he is the editor of the [[Journal of Automated Reasoning]]. Moreover, he focuses on programming language semantics, type systems and functional programming.<ref>[http://www.professoren.tum.de/nipkow-tobias Brief vita]</ref>
